üì° Validation Protocol
This repository utilizes the Git Commit Timestamp as an immutable proof-of-prediction.
1. Generation: A PIN is generated by an Observer Node (e.g., The Anchor, The Architect, The Wave).
2. Commit: The prediction is serialized into a locked JSON format and committed to the blockchain/repository.
3. Validation: Upon the arrival of the predicted date, the actual_outcome is verified against the locked predicted_window.
Note: Files in this repository are Immutable. Any alteration to a prediction post-commit invalidates the cryptographic trust chain.
